I went on my first Vox raid as an untwinked level 41 Cleric, back in maybe August of last year.  It was my first dragon raid ever (we lost BTW), and I had a lot of fun.  It was where I first met Vanz (/hugs), Franko (/bite), and many others.<br>
<br>
Anyway - my point.  After I was invited I had three days to prepare.  In those three days I managed to camp for/buy enough gear to achieve an unbuffed MR of 78 and a CR of 125.  This is why I get so pissed off when people say &quot;My resists suck but I'm sure I'll be OK&quot;.  If I could do it as a level 40 cleric - not exactly a money making machine here folks - then why can't YOU???<br>
<br>
These days my small dragon raiding is done with Command Performance, my bard.  She gets the benefit of stealing her big sister's resist gear, plus buffs, plus singing songs.  My gear is far from maxxed out but MR gets up to 298 and CR to 257.  needless to say Vox doesn't AoE me much.  She had to claw me to death last night =)<br>
